summary: Kolaj Magazine is the world’s only internationally-oriented art magazine dedicated to contemporary collage. Subscribe, order a...
caption:
Kolaj Magazine is the world’s only internationally-oriented art magazine dedicated to contemporary collage. Subscribe, order a copy, or collect back issues HERE

FROM KOLAJ #22

Cuts & Shifts

Poitiers, France-based collage artist Guillaume Chiron produces surreal, colourful artwork. He mixes the real with the unreal, the known with the unknown. First, he deconstructs multiple samples in a body of images produced and made available by the cultural industry. Then, he reconstructs and projects a new world, by selecting and bringing together some of these fragments. Sometimes, chance meets his work, and the magic operates. The lines of leaks follow each other and the perspectives coincide. New scenes appear, funny or incongruous, strange and reflexive. In Kolaj #22, we report on Chiron’s recent exhibition and a new book. MORE
